<% content_for :page_title, "Photos of the " + @plaque.title %>
<% content_for :title do %>
  Photos of <%= link_to(@plaque.title, @plaque) %>
<% end %>
<% content_for :page_subhead do %>
  <% if @plaque.photos.size < 1 %>
    <p>We don't have a photo of this plaque yet. You could be the first!</p>
  <% end %>
  <p>We display multiple photos of each plaque. We like close-ups as well as long-shots that set the scene. The closest shot will be used as the main image so that people can read the words.</p>
<% end %>
<%= render 'plaques/edit_bar', plaque: @plaque %>

<div class="row">
  <% @plaque.photos.detail_order.each do |photo| %>
    <div class="card col-xs-6 col-sm-4 col-md-3">
      <%= link_to photo_url(photo) do %>
        <% render photo %>
      <% end %>
      <span>By <%= link_to photo.photographer, photographer_url(photo.photographer.gsub(".","_").gsub("/","_")) if photo.photographer rescue photo.photographer %></span><br/>
      <%= form_for photo do |f| %>
        <p>This is a <%= f.collection_select :shot, Photo.shots, :to_s, :to_s, include_blank: true %></p>
        <%= f.submit t('buttons.save'), class: 'btn btn-primary pull-left' %>
        <%= link_to(t('buttons.edit'), edit_photo_path(photo), {class: 'btn btn-secondary pull-right', title: "edit photo"}) if current_user && current_user.is_admin? %>
      <% end %>
    </div>
  <% end %>
</div>

<div class="row">
  <h2>We do not store photos ourselves, we only link to them.</h2>
  <p>Open plaques connects and adds context to existing resources on the web instead of trying to own it all ourselves.
We use stable, open sources namely <a href="https://www.flickr.com/">Flickr</a>, <a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/">Wikimedia Commons</a> and <a href="https://www.geograph.org.uk/">Geograph</a>.
  The images are <a href="https://creativecommons.org/">Creative Commons</a> licenced and we attribute them to the copyright holder.</p>
</div>

<div class="row">
  <p><img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/7/79/Wiki-commons.png"/></p>
  <h2>I found, or would like to add, a photo of this plaque on Wikimedia Commons...</h2>
  <p>A great place to donate your image to the world is <a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/">Wikimedia Commons</a>.
It is free, fairly easy to use, and your image will [probably] live forever as part of the awesome Wikipedia platform.
When you are done, paste the url of the Wikimedia page in here and Open Plaques will link to the photo.</p>
  <p>
  <% @photo = Photo.new %>
  <%= form_for @photo do |f| %>
    <%= f.label(:url, "The Wikimedia photo page url is") %> <%= f.text_field :url %>
    <%= f.hidden_field :plaque_id, value: @plaque.id %>
    <%= submit_tag("Add it", :class=>'button secondary_button') %>
  <% end %>
  </p>
</div>

<div class="row">
  <h2>I'd like to add my photo via Flickr</h2>
  <ol><li>put it on <a href="https://www.flickr.com/" target="new">Flickr</a> (for free)</li>
  <li>give it a Creative Commons licence</li>
  <li>tag it <strong><%= @plaque.machine_tag %></strong></li>
  <li>add it to <a href="https://www.flickr.com/groups/openplaques/" target="new">our Flickr group</a></li>
  <li>wait 5 minutes</li>
  <li>it should now appear in the Flickr search of <a href="https://www.flickr.com/search/?q=<%= @plaque.machine_tag %>&m=machinetags&l=cc&content_type=1" target="new">photos tagged '<%= @plaque.machine_tag %>'</a></li>
  <li>wait for 24 hours and our servers should automatically find it and display it on our site</li>
  </ol>
  <br/>
  <h2>I did that, but my photo hasn&apos;t appeared!</h2>
  <p>Paste the url of the photo here and we will try to sort it out <%= form_tag("/photographers", method: "create") do %>
    <%= label_tag(:flickr_url, "Flickr photo url:") %>
    <%= text_field_tag(:flickr_url) %>
    <%= submit_tag("Search", :class=>'button secondary_button') %>
  <% end %></p>
  <br/>
  <h2>Nope, still not working</h2>
  <ol><li>still not there?</li>
  <li>Does your photo appear in the Flickr search of <a href="https://www.flickr.com/search/?q=<%= @plaque.machine_tag %>&m=machinetags&l=cc&content_type=1" target="new">photos tagged '<%= @plaque.machine_tag %>'</a>?</li>
  <li>if not, check that the licence is Creative Commons, i.e. it shouldn&apos;t say "All Rights Reserved"</li>
  <li>also, ensure that you haven&apos;t ticked the &apos;hidden from search&apos; setting. (On Flickr, go to your profile by clicking your username in top right hand corner, do you have "Hide your stuff from public searches" set to "no"?)</li>
  <li>a brand new Flickr account might not be included in their search immediately. Sometimes it waits until you have posted 5+ images. Enter your photo&apos;s url into the box below and we'll see what we can do...</li>
  <li>you can try <%= button_to "giving the automatic search a kick", controller: :plaques, action: :flickr_search, id: @plaque, class: "button secondary_button" %></li></ol>
</div>

<div class="row">
  <p><img src="http://www.geograph.org.uk/templates/basic/img/logo.gif"/></p>
  <h2>I found a photo of this plaque on Geograph...</h2>
  <p>
  <% @photo = Photo.new %>
  <%= form_for @photo do |f| %>
    <%= f.label(:url, "The photo page url is") %> <%= f.text_field :url %>
    <%= f.hidden_field :plaque_id, value: @plaque.id %> Please
    <%= submit_tag("Add it", :class=>'button secondary_button') %> to Open Plaques
  <% end %>
  </p>
</div>

<div class="row">
  <h2>Help, I really don&apos;t understand!</h2>
  <p>If this all proves too complicated, then have a chat with us via email. We are generally rather nice and want to help. You can <a href="https://openplaques.org/contact">email your photo</a> to us stating that you are happy for us to publish it as open data on your behalf and that you grant anyone in the world the right to re-use the image.</p>
</div>
